    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment for COU1 is Accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs required level 3) is partially mitigated by FEA sensitivity analysis demonstrating low QoI sensitivity to loading rate variation. The FEA model ensemble produces QoI predictions within pre-specified acceptance bounds for all three quantities of interest across N=11 experimental constructs at two independent laboratories. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
